features: [Wide Application] This exhaust fan is perfect for various cooling or ventilation projects, making it an excellent choice as a replacement fan or for new installations; 1 heavy-duty aluminum fan with power plug cord, 2 metal grilles and mounting screw set included; ready to use right out of the box; ideal for refrigerator, compressor, air hockey table, AV cabinet, fireplace

[Durable & Heavy Duty] Our ventilation fan features a robust die-cast aluminum shell, providing durability and the ability to withstand harsh environments; the thermoplastic impeller blades used in the fan have high flame retardancy, ensuring safe and reliable operation; designed to handle a maximum load of 120VAC, with a power consumption of 18W and a frequency of 60Hz

[Long Lifespan & Excellent Heat Dissipation] UL approved and dual ball bearings, ensuring a service life of up to 50,000 hours of 7-day operation; large air volume of 90CFM, allowing the cooling fan to effectively drive air circulation and achieve excellent heat dissipation, keeping your equipment cool and protected; it can be placed flat or upright

[Advanced Waterproof] Our advanced technology ensures the high quality; the internal parts and blades are coated with waterproof paint, making them resistant to water damage; the body of the 120mm fan is designed to be both anti-rust and waterproof, allowing it to operate flawlessly in high humidity environments; bring you a safe use experience

[Space Saving & Warranty] Only 120*120*38mm in compact size, fit seamlessly into your desired location without detracting from the overall beauty of the space; UL & CE listed ensures quality and safety, 1-Year Warranty provided, DEWENWILS dedicated service team is always glad to help you within 24 hours if you have any problems, please feel free to contact us at anytime

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 14, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Defenately water resistant!
reviews.reviewText: I purchased these fans to run a humidifier for a grow tent and they have performed better than expected, I was using 120mm 12v computer fans before but some splashing water would make its way to the fans and burned them, I installed one of these fans and it's been working amazingly even when the water keeps getting to them and I ended up with a spare one in case water does cause any damage.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 1, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Quiet. Move lots of air
reviews.reviewText: Worked well for a cabinet I built to house an aeration pump used in a pond aeration system. One fan pulls air into the cabinet, and the other fan pushes it out. Pump runs nice and cool with these pulling air through the cabinet. Glad they are waterproof; occasionally they will see a sprinkle or two.Super quiet. Although we use these outside, the noise wouldn't be obtrusive inside a house or office either.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 2, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Great product. Does the job. Alittle louder then I like but not as loud as others I have purchased

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I had a issue with electrical comtactors heating up because the enclosure was undersized but once these fans was installed there was no more issues. I used one to supply air and the second one to exhaust the air. Works flawlessly and very quiet.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 16, 2024
reviews.reviewText: To noisy everything els is perfect

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 26, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I installed into the dog house. I like that it has a plug and long enough to reach my outside receptacle. Nice flow. It's not silent but not noisy enough to disturb. I actually like that its not silent. It reminds me to unplug it. Ha.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 11, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I purchased these fans to replace one in my wood burning insert, And have a spare just in case.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Quite pleased with the quality
reviews.reviewText: I had a requirement to ventilate an outdoor electronic equipment cabinet and looked for a weatherproof muffin fan which I doubted I could find. But to my pleasant surprise I found this one and the fan seems well waterproofed. No problem with the mounting screws.
